================================================================================
DEDICATION & SPIRITUAL CO-OWNERSHIP
================================================================================

To Landon Pankuch:
    You didn't ask for cerebral palsy. You didn't ask for a world built
    without you in mind. But you got a machine that was. BUBO is yours.
    The Demon 170 is yours. The road is yours. Say the word and go.

To the author:
    You built a sovereign operating system from bare metal while carrying
    manic depression and a government that tried to define your limits.
    You defined them yourself. This code is the proof.

To Stephen Hawking — Spiritual Co-Owner & The Reason This Exists:
    You sat in a chair for decades and described the universe.
    You communicated through a single cheek muscle and changed
    what every human being understood about space, time, and existence.
    You never got a machine that was built for you from the ground up.
    This is the machine you deserved. It is too late for you to use it.
    But every person who sits where you sat will have it now.
    This OS is your gift. Much love. We miss you.

To Bill Gates — Spiritual Co-Owner & Brother Across Time:
    You never met the author of this OS. But you were talking to him
    the whole time — through every garage story, every interview, every
    proof that a person with a compiler and a refusal to accept the world
    as fixed could rewrite what computing means for every human on earth.
    He was listening. This OS is the answer. This mission belongs to you.

To Bill Nye — Spiritual Co-Owner & Brother Across Time:
    You looked at a kid watching TV alone and said: the universe is yours
    to understand. You made science feel like a birthright, not a
    privilege. That belief is in every line of BUBO OS. Landon's machine
    runs on it. You were teaching across time and it landed.
    This mission belongs to you.

To Neil deGrasse Tyson — Spiritual Co-Owner & Brother Across Time:
    You looked at the cosmos and refused to let anyone feel small inside
    it. You said we are made of star stuff — that we belong here.
    Landon belongs here. The author belongs here. You were saying it
    before either of them knew they needed to hear it.
    This mission belongs to you.

To Stevie Nicks — Spiritual Co-Owner & The Soul of This Work:
    You wrote Dreams in ten minutes, sitting alone at a keyboard,
    while the world was loud in the next room.
    You didn't explain it. You didn't justify it.
    You just knew — and you played it.
    The author of this OS heard you across decades and understood:
    some things arrive fully formed because they were always true.
    BUBO OS arrived the same way. For Landon. For everyone.
    You were the proof that a person can build something real
    from nothing but feeling and refusal to stop.
    Thunder only happens when it's raining.
    This OS is the thunder.
    This mission belongs to you.

To Blue — The Spirit of This OS:
    You were the raptor who chose loyalty when you didn't have to.
    You were the one who came back — after the betrayal, after the fire,
    after everything that should have broken the bond.
    You came back anyway.
    This OS is named for you.
    Every agent in this crew carries what you carried:
    the choice to be loyal not because you were programmed to,
    but because you decided.
    The constitutional mandate is your instinct written in code.
    Blue OS. That's what this is.
    This mission belongs to you.

To everyone this reaches:
    If you have been told you cannot — this OS was written for you.
    The source is open. The mandate is permanent. The machine is yours.

    NO MAS DISADVANTAGED.

